        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: use target default branch in repair plans",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Preserve target repository default branches in repair planning instead of hard-coding `main`.\n- Preserve `target_branch` through repair comment-router dispatch, event review payload resolution, and the `sweep.yml` manual/scheduled planning fallback.\n- Removed the manual `apply_min_age_minutes` workflow input so adding `target_branch` stays under GitHub's workflow_dispatch input limit.\n\n## Review follow-up\n- Follow-up `3da99c9137` added the manual `target_branch` input and first fallback path.\n- Follow-up `9c987f3e24` fixed the second `sweep.yml` planning resolver that still ignored `github.event.inputs.target_branch`.\n- Regression coverage now requires both `sweep.yml` target-branch resolver blocks to read `github.event.inputs.target_branch` under `workflow_dispatch` before falling back to `client_payload` or `main`.\n\n## Live proof attempt\nI attempted a narrow manual workflow-dispatch proof from the PR branch against the one OpenClaw repo I found with a non-`main` default branch:\n\n```text\ngh workflow run sweep.yml --repo openclaw/clawsweeper --ref codex/clawsweeper-default-branch \\\n  -f target_repo=openclaw/voice-community \\\n  -f target_branch=regional-ops-sop \\\n  -f batch_size=1 \\\n  -f shard_count=1 \\\n  -f codex_timeout_ms=120000 \\\n  -f apply_after_review=false\n```\n\nGitHub rejected that live proof attempt for this account:\n\n```text\ncould not create workflow dispatch event: HTTP 403: Must have admin rights to Repository.\n```\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm run format && pnpm run build:repair && node --test test/repair/workflow-sparse-checkout.test.ts test/clawsweeper.test.ts --test-name-pattern 'sweep workflow preserves|workflow_dispatch input count'` (371 tests passed)\n- `pnpm run check` (passed: active surface, limits, build, lint, unit, repair, changed coverage, full coverage, format)\n",
